name: ExtensionPatient_Contact
title: Cross-version Extension `R5.Patient.contact` for use in FHIR R4
description: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element `Patient.contact` for use in FHIR R4.
purpose:
This extension is part of the cross-version definitions generated to enable use of the
element `Patient.contact` as defined in FHIR R5
in FHIR R4.

The source element is defined as:
`Patient.contact` 0..* `BackboneElement`

Across FHIR versions, the element set has been mapped as:
*  R5: `Patient.contact` 0..* `BackboneElement`
*  R4B: `Patient.contact` 0..* `BackboneElement`
*  R4: `Patient.contact` 0..* `BackboneElement`

Following are the generation technical comments:
Element `Patient.contact` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `Patient.contact`, but has no comparisons.

element.short: A contact party (e.g. guardian, partner, friend) for the patient
element.definition: A contact party (e.g. guardian, partner, friend) for the patient.
element.comment: Contact covers all kinds of contact parties: family members, business contacts, guardians, caregivers. Not applicable to register pedigree and family ties beyond use of having contact.
